OL,3,CPerranporth man recalls being swept up
OL,4,Cby the Boxing Day tsunami 20 years ago
OL,6,FWhen Daniel returned home he said he
OL,7,Fcarried around a lot of fear "when we
OL,8,Ffirst came back my partner and I
OL,9,Fcouldn't even be on the beach when
OL,10,Fthere were stormy seas. One of my best
OL,11,Fmates took me for a surf soon after
OL,12,Fand I remember being so scared, but
OL,13,Ftime was able to heal".
OL,15,FThe experience of being swept up in
OL,16,Fthe tsunami changed the course of
OL,17,FDaniel's life and led him to work in
OL,18,Fthe humanitarian aid sector, now with
OL,19,Fthe Cornish charity ShelterBox.
