OL,3,CPerranporth man recalls being swept up
OL,4,Cby the Boxing Day tsunami 20 years ago
OL,6,F"As an emergency co-ordinator, I get
OL,7,Fto go around the world supporting
OL,8,Fcommunities after disaster to help
OL,9,Fthem get back into shelter, which is
OL,10,Fthat first springboard to recovery and
OL,11,FI suppose it's calibrated me to that
OL,12,Fbeing that's like a North Star, you
OL,13,Fknow, wanting to help people".
OL,15,FThe apocalyptic scenes of destruction
OL,16,Fwere an impetus to act for many
OL,17,Fincluding Mark Boeck, a Cornish
OL,18,Ffirefighter at the time, who
OL,19,Fvolunteered to deliver aid to
OL,20,FIndonesia in April 2005.
